I examined UserAccountController.signupForNewAccount and the related request/response DTOs.

- The controller maps POST /api/account/signup to method signupForNewAccount and expects a JSON request body of type SignupRequestBody.
- The SignupRequestBody class exposes JSON properties account_username, account_email, and account_password.
- On success the controller returns a UserAccountDTO, which serializes to JSON properties account_id, account_username, and account_email.
- The controller can throw IllegalArgumentException for invalid email format and AccountInformationTakenException when username or email are already taken; these map naturally to 400 and 409 error responses respectively.
- The method does not set an explicit HTTP status, so the successful response is modeled as 200 OK carrying the UserAccountDTO JSON.

